The paper deals with the problem of exact localization of multiple objects with noisy data, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that involves random illumination, which is a technique used in information theory and signal processing. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the Lasso and one-step thresholding (OST) recovery methods, which are machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category. The paper also presents numerical evidence to support its claims, which involves simulations and computations. Hence, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible sub-categories.
